Transfer learning and fine-tuning

Transfer learning consists of taking features learned on one problem, and leveraging them on a new, similar problem. For instance, features from a model that has learned to identify racoons may be useful to kick-start a model meant to identify skunks.

Variable

Writing Layer and Model objects from scratch.

One of the central abstractions in Keras is the Layer class. A layer encapsulates both a state (the layer’s “weights”) and a transformation from inputs to outputs (a “call”, the layer’s forward pass).

Writing your own callbacks

A callback is a powerful tool to customize the behavior of a Keras model during training, evaluation, or inference. Examples include callback_tensorboard() to visualize training progress and results with TensorBoard, or callback_model_checkpoint() to periodically save your model during training.
Rick Chao, Francois Chollet, Tomasz Kalinowski
